The course begins with an on-site session where learning metaphors  and new learning paradigm with its main components will be systematically introduced. The course continues with independent e-learning sessions, where the topics will be elaborated using course study materials, recommended literature which will be reinforced in the seminars. The students conduct a micro-study to understand how to capture the elements of the new learning paradigm in learning situations. Students analyse the studied situations and, based on what they have learned, propose alternative innovative solutions that meet the goal.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course provides a general and systematic overview of learning metaphors, new learning paradigm, also their characteristic learning and teaching methods. In addition, it guides students to relevant scientific literature and prepares them to shape educational innovation based on the acquired knowledge.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student: (1) has a systematic overview about learning metaphors and new learning paradigm and their characteristic learning and teaching methods; (2) has a general overview about problem-solving, inquiry-based learning, collaborative learning, and self-regulation and reflection; (3) has a responsible attitude towards educational innovation; (4) has skills to analyse and plan for apt learning situations.
